# Pattern Evaluation - LCP-UML-9 (2026-03-23)

- Total classes/records inspected: 13 (5 controllers, 8 request/DTO records)
- Patterns found (unique): 5 — Dependency Injection, Transaction Script, Unit of Work (EF DbContext), Optimistic Concurrency (row version tokens), Data Transfer Object
- Pattern density: 5 / 13 = 0.38
- Overall grade: D+ (controllers are thin wrappers over EF Core with DI and concurrency safeguards, but they bypass domain/services, expose persistence concerns, and lack interface-driven abstraction; SRP/ISP/ DIP mostly unmet).

