## Gaps & Risks
- No domain entity implementations or repository/service layers present; controllers talk directly to `AppDbContext`, making persistence concerns leak across the API.
- No abstractions/interfaces for data access or domain policies; Dependency Inversion violated and unit testing difficult without heavy mocks of EF Core.
- Validation and business rules are minimal; transactions are started per action but without domain invariants, risking inconsistent state.
- Missing implementations for Domain/Infrastructure folders (only empty directories), suggesting incomplete architecture and broken layering.

## Improvement Suggestions
1) Introduce application services and repositories (interfaces + implementations) to move transaction/EF logic out of controllers and satisfy DIP/ISP.
2) Add domain entities/value objects with behavior plus validators; controllers should map DTOs to commands handled by the application layer.
3) Centralize concurrency and transaction handling in a unit-of-work service/decorator rather than per-controller code to reduce duplication.
4) Add automated tests around transaction boundaries and concurrency conflicts once the abstractions exist.
